{"key":"processedPost-14069847","value":{"id":14069847,"first":14066596,"last":14070203,"when":1299336228,"utime":"03/05/11 04:43 PM","content":"Use rice bran as a direct replacement for brown rice flour.&nbsp; It's superior in every way.&nbsp; If you're having trouble with colonization, check your inoculant.<br /><br />Mix it as shown in the <a href=\"http://www.mushroomvideos.com/BRF-Pf-Tek\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">videos</a>.&nbsp; Mix the water and verm first, and then slowly add the rice flour.&nbsp; The mix should look dry when you load your jars.&nbsp; If it's too wet, it won't colonize.<br /><br />One thing to remember, rice bran is more nutritious than rice flour, so it will colonize somewhat slower. This is normal and the extra time colonizing is made up for with extra performance at fruiting.<br />RR","title":"Re: Rice bran help","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}